org.flexiblepower.ral.values

Class UncertainMeasure<Q extends javax.measure.quantity.Quantity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.flexiblepower.ral.values.UncertainMeasure<Q>
  • Type Parameters:
    Q - Quantity of measurement, see Commodity
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<javax.measure.Measurable<Q>>, javax.measure.Measurable<Q>

    public class UncertainMeasure<Q extends javax.measure.quantity.Quantity>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, javax.measure.Measurable<Q>
    This class is being used to express uncertainty about a value. It does not prescribe a particular distribution, such as a normal distribution. Instead UncertainMeasure provides the mean value as well as the ranges in which 68 and 95 percent of the values fall. For both ranges a lower and upper bound is given. This flexible solution also allows the expression of asymmetric distributions.
